@startuml
' IC MS Intent Version Lifecycle State Diagram
hide empty description

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #5a7a9a
  FontSize 12
  FontColor #1a1a2e
  ArrowColor #5a7a9a
  ArrowFontSize 11
  ArrowFontColor #333366
  AttributeFontSize 11
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #fffde7
  BorderColor #d6b656
  FontSize 11
  FontColor #333300
}
skinparam legend {
  BackgroundColor #f0f4f8
  BorderColor #5a7a9a
  FontSize 11
}

title IC MS — Intent Version Lifecycle State Diagram

' ── Entry ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
[*] --> Acknowledged : version accepted

' ── States ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
state Acknowledged #d4e6f1 : Syntactically admitted,\nawaiting change handling
state InProgress #d5f5e3 : Change execution\nin progress
state Active #2ecc71 : Network / service confirmed\n(activeVersion)
state Degraded #f9e79f : Assurance degradation\ndetected
state Paused #e8daef : Controlled pause
state Standby #d6eaf8 : Non-active retained\nversion (fallback candidate)
state Rejected #f5cba7 : Validation / policy\nrejection
state Failed #f1948a : Change or runtime\nfailure
state Terminated #aab7b8 : Closed — no longer\nruntime-active
state Retired #d5d8dc : Administrative /\nversion-governance archive

' ── Primary version change lifecycle ───────────────────────────────────────
Acknowledged --> InProgress : change starts
InProgress --> Active : network/service confirmed
InProgress --> Failed : change failed
InProgress --> Rejected : validation / policy rejection

' ── Operational runtime lifecycle ──────────────────────────────────────────
Active --> Degraded : assurance degradation
Active --> Paused : controlled pause
Active --> Failed : runtime failure
Active --> Terminated : teardown / delete completed
Active --> Standby : newer version becomes activeVersion

Degraded --> Active : recovered
Degraded --> Paused : controlled pause
Degraded --> Failed : unrecoverable failure
Degraded --> Terminated : teardown / delete completed
Degraded --> Standby : newer version becomes activeVersion

Paused --> Active : resumed
Paused --> Failed : unrecoverable failure
Paused --> Terminated : teardown / delete completed
Paused --> Standby : newer version becomes activeVersion

' ── Closure and governance lifecycle ───────────────────────────────────────
Rejected --> Terminated : close rejected version
Failed --> Terminated : close failed version
Standby --> Acknowledged : restart Intent version change lifecycle
Standby --> Terminated : explicit termination / no longer retained
Terminated --> Retired : administrative archive decision
Retired --> [*]

' ── Notes ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
note top of Acknowledged
Do not allow another newer candidate version when a newer version already exists in Acknowledged or InProgress.
end note

note right of Active
activeVersion points to the version currently confirmed as active by IC MS projection from IA outcomes.
end note

note bottom of Standby
Standby is a non-active retained Intent version.
It may be used as a fallback / restartable candidate,
but must re-enter through Acknowledged.
No direct Standby to Active transition.
No direct Standby to Retired transition.
end note

note right of Retired
Retired is an administrative / version-governance archival state — not a runtime/network state.
Only Terminated may transition to Retired.
No other state may transition directly to Retired.
end note

legend right
Version replacement behaviour
──────────────────────────────────────────────
When a newer version becomes activeVersion:
• Previous Active / Degraded / Paused to Standby
• Previous Rejected / Failed to Terminated
• Standby can restart only via Acknowledged
• Only Terminated can move to Retired
endlegend

@enduml
